===Etymology===
From both the {{etyl|ML.|lang=en}} {{term|academicus|acadēmicus|lang=la}} and the {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|académique|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|academia|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἀκαδημικός|tr=akademeikos|lang=grc}}, from {{term|Ἀκαδημία|tr=Akademia||the location where Plato taught|lang=grc}} (alternative form: [[Ἀκαδήμεια]]) ; compare {{term|academy|lang=en}}.{{rfscript|grc}}<ref name=WI3>Gove, Philip Babcock, ed. ''Webster's Third International Dictionary of the English Language Unabridged.'' Springfield: G. & C. Merriam Co., 1976.</ref>

